This paper discusses the security and privacy issues related to web browser extensions, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and web technologies (cs.WEB). The paper also proposes a method for identifying unwanted modifications to web content, which involves analyzing the provenance of the content, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
